																		No Good Deed Goes Unpunished
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1372582&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203530" alt="Jacob Conwell" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1372582)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;" >Jacob Conwell</a></span> <span class="odate time_1483988859 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Jan 2017 19:07</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2723481">
									

<p>This has been a tale that’s been in my sandbox since way back in November. I ended up putting it off to work on finishing the <a href="/wayfarers-hub">Wayfarers</a> series of tales, and to work on <a href="/aboard-the-train-to-berlin">Xmas</a> <a href="/where-they-kept-their-copies">Exchange</a> projects. Now, however, it is finally here.</p>
<p>Inspired in part by the song <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PoxzYuZm3EA">I’m Going to Change Your Life</a> by The Thermals, I wanted to write a tale that explored Vincent Anderson’s life as both an employer and as a member of a (now broken) family in comparison to the personal life of his SCPF nemesis Agent Sasha Merlo.</p>
<p>Special thanks are in order for Taffeta, Greenwolf, Agent MacLeod, Roget, TyGently, TwistedGears, A Random Day, Randomini, Zyn, Decibelle, Orionbasher, Rimple, minmin, AbsentmindedNihilist, ProcyonLotor, LurkD, and Cyantreuse, all of whom provided great feedback when I pestered them with this as a draft.</p>
<p>Double Secret Special Thanks to Decibelle for use of her character Rose Labelle.</p>
<p>Hope you enjoy the tale.</p>
<p><em>JC</em></p>

