			<div class="content" id="post-content-4837970">
									

<p>Ayyyy, the Thermals! Always nice to see them, although I definitely had <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O4hh1YhDfbA">another song</a> going through my head as I read this.</p>
<p>At this point &quot;well-written and compelling&quot; goes without saying, but I'll say it again. Maybe it's just me reading these in relatively quick succession, but I have to say that I didn't really feel bad for Anderson. Like, this certainly humanized him and provided him with more characterization, but Phineas is right. He's a hypocrite who demands loyalty and adoration, but repeatedly transgresses against people if it's convenient, only to try to make it up with presents. So, fully realized character, yes. Worthy of sympathy, not really.</p>

							</div>

								
					
